President Trump held a press conference to announce the signing of the omnibus budget bill and discuss various topics including trade deals, defense spending, border security, and the opioid crisis. He expressed disappointment with certain aspects of the bill but emphasized the need to fund the military. He also discussed the progress made in combating the opioid epidemic and the importance of border security. The President mentioned the ongoing negotiations with South Korea and the positive developments in trade deals with other countries. He also addressed concerns about the impact of tariffs on the stock market and expressed confidence in the U.S.-China relationship.